cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "scopusflow: a reproducible workflow layer over pybliometrics for Scopus searches"
abstract: >-
  A reproducible workflow layer over pybliometrics for Scopus searches. It builds
  reproducible search plans, retrieves records with rate-limit handling and
  resumable caching, normalises results to a stable tidy schema, tracks changes in
  DOIs between runs, compares publication trends across topics and exports to
  formats used by downstream bibliometric tools. It is the Python twin of the R
  package scopusflow.
type: software
